<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08112d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08112d">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08112d"> 112(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> incest applauded in Eden</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><i>Undenam Caino uxor? Utique ex filiabus Adae, quas multas habuit &hellip;, vel saltem ex Adae nepotibus. &hellip; Initio mundi necesse fuit sorores fratribus nubere, ut observant Augustinus, Chrysostomus et Theodoretus, quod alias jure naturae vetitum est.</i> <br><font color="green">[Where did Cain&apos;s wife come from? Undoubtedly from the daughters of Adam&mdash;and he had many&mdash;or at least from the descendants of Adam. At the beginning of the world it was necessary that sisters marry brothers, as Augustine, Chrysostomus and Theodoretus observe, which is otherwise prohibited by natural law.]</font> <small> Thomas Josephus Lamy, <a name="TJLC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TJLC"><cite title="source">Commentarium in librum geneseos</cite></a> (1884) 257</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
